<br>
If you are doing the same sort of thing he is (fulfilling your desires at the expense of others, breaking the rules, etc.) then what he is doing isn't really that wrong, see? At least in his mind. It makes it so easy for him to pull out the 'you guys are no different from me, and you deserved it' excuse. He desperately wants you down at his level -- the illusion that you are is a key part of his self-justifying mantra, a huge part of what keeps him mentally comfy doing what he does. Remember that, and don't give him what he wants.<br>
<br>
You can't give up the moral high ground to deal with the folks wallowing in the mud, or you wind up just as filthy as they are. On the other hand, completely shunning jerks like him starts to really hurt after a while. See, even if he can be all 'smart' and 'trick' you into accepting him in another guise or sneak into a guild by stealth or lying, he knows deep down in the depths of his slimy little heart that you don't really like him. He knows nobody really likes him, they just like his facade or believe his lies or whatever. And that hurts more than a lost corpse in a bad zone or a PvP ambush.<br>
<br>
