Seems to me that Srir hasn't seen any benefit to having compassion, kindness, or honor in his daily life.  If he was <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> roleplaying</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a bastard that would be one thing, as to actually create a ficticious persona requires some understanding of its make-up, and thereby we could assume that he'd seen enough of the noble morals to enable a contrived form in character.  Alas, this is not the case.<br>
<br>
The mere fact that Srir plays on the kindness of others as a weakness only shows that in his daily life, there is no benefit or strength gained by loving words or smiles, gentle carresses or the friends you gain by pleasant small talk.  A pity really, Srir doesn't seem so much a true bastard as an unloved loner who despite actions to the contrary does seek to have companions...how many times has he joined a guild now?<br>
<br>
Of course the best thing to do in such a case is to help the person find a place where they can fit it.  I will gladly offer my help in making life as miserable as possible for him here in order to get him over to an X-Box.<br>
